description: Recently sold: $218,400. Private Country Living in Wrenshall's Pleasant Valley: 72.5 Acre Hobby Farm Homestead with a Cute & Cozy 2 BR Expansion Bungalow and Outbuildings.  Start your day with sunrise views at breakfast in the updated, light-filled kitchen, and appreciate amazing sunsets from the comfort of your living room.  Large windows allow you to experience the Southern Exposure and views of the park-like property.  The main level hosts the Master Bedroom, 2nd Bedroom and Full Bath.  The 2nd level Expansion offers room for living/hobby/office space and storage.  The lower level is semi-finished with bar area, complete with propane fireplace, and shower/sink. The well-designed wrap-around deck is the perfect spot to barbeque.  Control how you heat - this home is serviced by a propane boiler and exterior pressurized wood boiler.  The 21x16 Garage serves as a rustic workshop, and is all set up with electricity, workbenches and wood stove.  You can store your equipment, gear and toys in the lean-to pole barn.  Many barn dances (with 100+ guests) have been held in the huge hay loft. It holds around 5,000 square bales of hay.  Approx. 5+ acres are fence-post ready for new install of electrical wire, and the property invites horses, cattle, pigs and pets; it's complete with a chicken coop!   There is a duck pond and wildlife galore.  Mowed trails throughout the property for horse back riding or any use on your own private park like setting.  Multiple deer stands are already in place with abundant wildlife.  Star gaze from a beautiful camping spot with fire pit on top of the hill overlooking the valley with the river.  Experience total privacy. Easy access to The Soo Line Trail.

description:
Recently sold: $220,000. This old fashioned square log home sits back, down a private driveway. The home has had many updates since 2016 including new log chinking, a large main-level bathroom remodel, laundry area added upstairs (room for a large second bathroom), shed dormers added to the front, and new cedar siding placed on the addition and second level of the home among other updates. The upstairs bedrooms (2+)  are accessible via an open rebar railing catwalk. The home has many rustic and unique touches and is one-of-a-kind! 

There is a private well and propane in floor radiant heat. This is easily supplemented using the wood-burning stove, which had a new blower fan installed in 2017. The large storage/mud room off of the kitchen is multi purpose and has much room for storage.

As you pull in the driveway, there is an older large garage with additional room for a shop or toy storage. The large out building has running water and power and is set up for small stable use. Acreage is semi wooded and a portion has been used for crops. A natural stream also flows along the western side of the property.

This home has potential for a primary residence or as a cabin getaway not far from Duluth, Cloquet, and Superior. It was once a CSA (community supported agriculture) farm and a pig farm; it has great soil!

Make this charming getaway your very own!
